					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10037139#post-4368369</guid>
				<title>Re: Question, Please Correct Me If I’m Wrong</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10037139/scp-4975#post-4368369</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 19 Sep 2019 10:16:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Scented_Shadow</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2206112</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The implication is that 4975 is somehow in two places at once, both in the cell and in its hometown forest. However, the latter version is only perceptible to its victim; as you could tell, no one but the dying man could see, hear, or even touch it. The Foundation locked 4975 up to stop it from killing, but unfortunately for them, death is inevitable and if someone's time is up, they've just got to go. A measly little containment chamber wasn't gonna stop that. The man had cancer (as implied by him receiving chemotherapy), and was simply destined to die that day. 4975 was just doing its job by making it happen cap'n.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10037139#post-4367904</guid>
				<title>Question, Please Correct Me If I’m Wrong</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10037139/scp-4975#post-4367904</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Sep 2019 19:54:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DesertStorm11</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5592747</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><em>“Note: According to surveillance footage, at this exact time, SCP-4975 had stopped rotating its neck and was instead staring motionless at the southeastern corner of its containment cell.“</em></p> <p>It says this during the addendum. It seems to me that SCP-4975 can become invisible, but I don’t think that’s stated in the description. Also, is 4975 also somehow teleporting its being to Germany, even though it’s in containment? I get the fact that it stops moving it’s head when it’s killing a target, but the other two parts are unclear.</p> <p>I could be missing something obvious, but I’ve pretty thoroughly read this article a few times.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
